Ekurhuleni law enforcement officials have visited several companies that recently reported Covid-19 outbreaks. JOHANNESBURG - Ekurhuleni law enforcement officials have visited several companies that recently reported COVID-19 outbreaks. They're trying to figure out how 24-staff members of a Dischem branch in Boksburg contracted the virus. The officials also visited a Unilever factory in the same area where 34-staff members tested positive for COVID-19. READ: SA lockdown: Labour minister says UIF under extreme pressure Ekurhuleni law enforcement says it will be keeping a close eye on sites with confirmed cases of COVID-19. Gauteng has 1,101 confirmed cases. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.